[Result "*"]

1. --
{ Nothing has changed after my first course. Yet to brag about my notable achievements 😊 once again, here are some of them. I won the Asian Championship in 2016 and was a member of the bronze-winning Indian team at the 2014 Olympiad. I have also reached the third round of the World Cup two times in the year 2015 and 2017. In those World Cup appearances, I beat formidable opponents such as former World Champion Ruslan Ponomariov and my compatriot Pentala Harikrishna. I also represented India in various official events like World teams, Asian teams, and the Olympiad. Of course, to mention that I am desperately waiting for the OTB events to begin to extend my horizons and earn many more achievements in the future😊. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Special Mentions"]
[Result "*"]

1. --
{ Before proceeding on to the course, special mentions to the James Bond of Chess :  , Frank James Marshall. He was the first master to have exclusively played the Jaenisch Gambit, which occurred in 33 of his games in the 1900s. And in the 21st century, the Azeri King, Temouir Radjabov  (Raja means King in the Hindi Language)  😊 has brought the system back into fashion.  He was holding his ground against the elite players. Thanks to the excellent efforts of these two players, the Jaenisch Gambit had made its way back into fashion. Then, the system begins to slowly decline in the post-2005 era as Black found it difficult to sustain it. Once again, it has come back into play as I am here to revive it and restore the faith of this opening in the city of Gambits 😊. I would be glad to be known as the Bruce Wayne of this opening if it comes back to life at the elite level 😊. I wish good times for the Jaenisch Gambit ahead! }
*

