13. c3 Bb6 14. Nxb6
{ 14.b3?!  Qxe4  15.Qd2  Bf5  was slightly better in Smeets, J @@StartBracket@@2643@@EndBracket@@ -Pruijssers, R @@StartBracket@@2549@@EndBracket@@ Amsterdam 2013. I should mention here that the Dutch Grandmaster Pruijssers is also an expert in this opening as upon analyzing I found many of his games with success. }
14... axb6 15. c4
{ Played in two games of Harikrishna-Nihal 2018 Tata Steel Rapid and Shankland-Gareyev 2015 and here comes an astounding novelty missed in both of the games. }
15... Qe6 { Targeting the c4-pawn. } 16. b3 Qxe4 17. Qxe4 Nxe4 18. f3
{ This was the idea of White when playing 16.b3 but here comes a nice trick after... }
18... Nc3 { The super tricky Knight! } 19. Bb2 Bf5 20. Bxc3 Bxd3
{ And the endgame is equal. } *

