15. e5 { 15.Nxb6  axb6  16.e5  transposes to the text with 15.e5. } 15... dxe5
16. Nxe5 { 16.Nxb6  axb6  17.Nxe5  Qh5  transposes simply. } 16... Qh5 17. Nxb6
axb6
{ White has an extra pawn but like in most of the cases in this opening, the opposite-colored bishops on the board come to the rescue. The aspect of having opposite-colored bishops increases the drawing tendency. Next on the cards is ...Ba6. }
18. b3 Re8 19. f4 Nd7 { Changing the active Knight on e5. } 20. a4 Nxe5 21.
fxe5 Ba6 22. c4 Qxe5 23. Bf4 Qd4+
