{ Of course we take with the pawn to support e5. } 8. d4
{ The standard thrust against Black's centre, to which we respond back with... }
8... e4 9. Ne5 { is ineffective here after... } 9... fxe5 10. Qh5+ Kd7 11. Qf7+
{ 11.Qxe5  Bd6  12.Qxd5  Qf6  and Black has stabilized the position  and if   12.Qf5+  then  12...Ke7   12...Ke8  allows  13.Qh5+  13.Bg5  Ke8  and both of the Queens are under attack which gives Black the upperhand. }
11... Qe7 12. Qxd5+ Qd6 13. Qf7+ Be7 { No draw! } 14. d5 Rf8 15. dxc6+ bxc6 16.
Qxh7 Qf6
{ 16...cxb5  will be faced by  17.Bg5  and White will be able to create some counterplay. With the text move we attack the f2-pawn and White's position looks scary. }
