4... fxe4
{ White was already threatening to take on f5, so this looks logical. } 5. dxe4
Nf6 6. O-O
{ Here Black has two plans. Either to develop the Bishop to c5 or e7 by 6.... d6 followed by 7...Be7. The first option lands the Bishop to a more active square but the drawback is that it loses the e5-pawn. The second is more of strengthening the center but then the Black Bishop on f8 remains passive. We will be looking at both of these options in different chapters. }
6... Bc5
{ As destiny chooses it, my repertoire is once again filled with the Bishop landing on c5. Perhaps you will have a clue of what I am talking about if you have checked my first Chessable course: Lifetime Repertoires: Sethuraman's 1. e4 e5 with the Black side. Black develops the Bishop to c5, to a more active square to put pressure on the f2-pawn followed by O-O. Of course, the drawback is that we lose the e5-pawn after   7.Bxc6  which will be dealt with in the 6th chapter. }
7. Nc3 d6 8. Be3
{ White's plan is to open up the f-file for his Rook after the exchange of the dark-squared Bishops. I doubt it creates any pressure as our Knight on f6 simply sabotages the f-file. If   8.Na4  Bb6  9.Bc4  then  9...Na5  and White has to go back with his Bishop allowing us to castle. }
8... Bxe3 9. fxe3 O-O
{ On a closer look, White is structurally doing bad, so he has to rely on his immediate threats after... }
10. Bc4+ Kh8 11. Ng5 { Planning to invade on f7. } 11... Qe8
{ Only move as   11...Qe7  will be met by  12.Nd5  and its losing. } 12. Nd5
{ All of White's pieces are penetrating but we are in time to rescue after... }
12... Qg6 13. h4
{ 13.Nxc7  Qxg5  14.Nxa8  Bg4  is the point and we get the piece on a8. } 13...
Bg4 14. Be2 { The play becomes forced now after... } 14... Bxe2 15. Qxe2 Nxe4
16. Nxc7 Rab8
{ Precise as   16...Rac8?  would be a mistake because of  17.Nce6!  Rxf1  18.Rxf1  Nxg5  19.Nxg5  h6  and  20.Qg4  attacks the Rook on c8 with the threat of Nf7+ at the same time. Hence the Rook is ill placed on c8 which comes under attack. So, it is important to place the Rook on b8. }
17. Nce6 { 17.Qd3  Nxg5  18.Qxg6  hxg6  is also equal. } 17... Rxf1+ 18. Qxf1
Nf6 { And the attack is sabotaged. } *

