10. Nh4 { The idea is to bring the Queen into play after Bxf6. } 10... Be6 11.
Bxf6 { 11.Nxf6  gxf6  12.Be3  Bb6  is fine for Black. } 11... gxf6 12. Qh5
{ Now you see the point behind Nh4 as White simply controls the f5-square. }
12... Rg8
{ Time for some counterplay, otherwise our position will be doomed to passivity. }
13. Qh6 Bxd5 { The active Knight on d5 has be to eliminated. } 14. exd5 Ne7 15.
Qxf6+ { 15.Bd3  Rg7  and Black is safe securing the h7-pawn. } 15... Rg7
{ The d5-pawn is hanging now. } 16. Rad1 Qg8
{ The a8-Rook is coming to f8 and the d5-pawn is also under attack which gives Black a slightly better position. }
*

