11. Nxb6
{ White gets to exchange the dangerous Bishop on b6 and remains a pawn up. The fact is that the opposite-colored Bishops on the board increases the drawing tendency. }
11... axb6 12. Re1 Qg6
{ With ...d5 to follow next, Black will free up his position. Stockfish often overestimates this position as slightly better for White but LC0 @@StartBracket@@ Leela chess Zero@@EndBracket@@ simply calls it fine for Black. I trust LC0 and as well my own mind which tells me that this position is close to equality. }
