{ White has grabbed the central pawn but of course we do have some compensation in the form of the Bishop pair. }
8... O-O { A couple of moves here are possible. } 9. Nc3 d6 10. Nxc6
{ On hindsight, White captures a pawn but lends free play for Black after... }
10... Qe8 11. Nd4
{ 11.Nd5  Nxd5  12.exd5  Ba6  and we are winning.  If   11.b4  it will be met by the intermediate  11...Ba6  and Black is totally fine. }
11... Nxe4 12. Nxe4 Qxe4
{ The active Queen combined with two Bishops is a deadly combination. } 13. c3
Qg6 14. f3 Bh3 15. Rf2 Rae8
{ And the active Black pieces clearly proves sufficient compensation. } *

