14... axb6 15. c4
{ Played in two games of Harikrishna-Nihal 2018 Tata Steel Rapid and Shankland-Gareyev 2015. Here comes an astounding novelty missed in both the games. }
15... Qe6 { Targeting the c4-pawn. } 16. e5 Nh5 17. exd6 Be2
{ is the point! By next move, we will support the Queen on e6. White cannot save both the Rook and the Knight at the same time. }
18. d7
{ Prevents ...Rae8 which will support the Queen on e6. By this move, White borrows some time to rescue his Rook and the Knight. }
18... Rf7
{ As we cannot take the pawn with the Queen, we bring the Rook to capture this annoying pawn on d7. }
19. f3 Rxd7 20. Nf4 { 20.Rf2  Re8  is fine for us. } 20... Nxf4 21. Bxf4 Qxc4
{ And White escapes with the Rook to f2 which leaves the position balanced. } *

