Kh8 10. Bxc6 bxc6 11. Qxc6
{ We have clear compensation in the form of the Bishop pair. } 11... Rb8
{ Preparing to bring the Bishop to b7. } 12. Qa4 Bg4
{ Trigerring the Bishop to attack the f3-Knight. } 13. Nd2 Nh5
{ With strong counterplay as the Knight is invading the f4 square creating a stir in the hornet's nest. }
