{ Taking on e4 would be huge blunder as for instance   11...Nxe4??  then  12.Nxe7  Qxe7  13.Qd5  loses the piece. }
12. b4 Nc6 13. b5 Nb8
{ Although White has expanded on the queenside successfully creating some space, we are doing fine as our centre is intact and hard to break. }
