[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqk2r/pppp2pp/2n2n2/1Bb1p3/4P3/2PQ1N2/PP1N1PPP/R1B1K2R b KQkq - 0 8"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Find the standard idea here. } 8... a5
{ The idea of the move 8...a5 is that it simply prevents White from expanding and attacking our powerful Bishop on c5 with b4. }
9. Nf1 { With the plan of bringing the Knight or the Bishop to e3. } 9... d6
{ Be careful and do not blunder our c5-Bishop after   9...O-O??  which will lose on the spot to  10.Qc4+ }
10. Qc4
{ For the time-being, the move prevents short castle and also ...Be6 plans. }
10... Qe7 { Looks logical to prepare ...Be6. } 11. Ne3 Bd7
{ 11...Be6  is not possible due to  12.Nd5  and we cannot take the Knight on d5 with our f6-Knight as it will lead to a double attack. That explains our placement of the Bishop on d7. }
12. Nd5 Nxd5 { Now we are free to take on d5. } 13. exd5 Nd8 14. Bxd7+ Qxd7
{ The Knight will get re-routed to f7 next. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
