[SetUp "1"]

{ How to continue? } 15... b5
{ An unexpected cold shower for White as now he is unable to defend the d5-pawn. }
16. Qc3 Qxd5
{ The central pawn is too much of importance as always :@@EndBracket@@, as we even weaken our King slightly by the b5 advance to gain it. Without the light-squared Bishops on the board, there is nothing to worry about our King safety. }
17. Be3 Rhe8 18. a4 { Aiming for some attack. } 18... b4
{ Of course to close the a-file. } 19. Nxb4 Bxb4 20. Qxd4 Qxd4 21. Bxd4 Re2
{ And the Rook enters the second rank. } *

