[SetUp "1"]

{ Our pieces are passive and White has full control over the f-file. How do we create counterplay? }
22... Rc8 { Sometime in the future we can break open with ...c6. } 23. c4
{ 23.Rf1  c6 !  Now we see the point of ...Rc8.  24.c4  e4  25.Qd1  Qe5  Centralization!  26.dxc6  Rxc6  Black gains sufficient activity and it was draw in the correspondence game of Vetter,G  @@StartBracket@@2394@@EndBracket@@-Voetter,H @@StartBracket@@2380@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2010. }
23... a5 { Fixing the pawn structure. } 24. Kf1 Qh4
{ Was equal in Edwards,K @@StartBracket@@2212@@EndBracket@@ -Burmeister,F @@StartBracket@@2217@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2018. Black has an active Queen and even though White has control over the f-file, he cannot really benefit from it. }
