[SetUp "1"]

{ Find the key move here. } 14... Nb4
{ Challenging both the d5-Knight and the d3-Bishop. } 15. Ne3
{ 15.Nxb4  will be met by an intermezzo with  15...Bg4  16.Qg3  and then  16...Bxb4 }
15... Qh6 16. Nhf5 Qf4 17. Qe2 d5
{ And all of the Black pieces are well coordinated. Moreover, the d3-Bishop can be taken anytime obtaining the Bishop pair. }
