[SetUp "1"]

{ How do we free ourselves from White's bind on f5? } 16... f5
{ In time, before White occupies the f5-square. } 17. Nxf5 Rg5 18. Nh4 Qh6
{ All the pieces are coming in. } 19. g3 Qxh4 20. Qf6+ Kg8
{ And White cannot take the piece back on e7:   21.Qxe7  due to  21...Rxg3  and the Queen is lost. }
21. Kh1 Qh5 22. g4
{ Only move as   22.Qxe7  would lose to  22...Qf3+  23.Kg1  Rg7  and the d3 pieces falls apart. }
22... Qh4 23. Qxe7 Rxg4
{ An equal game with opposite-colored Bishops on the board. } *

