{ A mindblowing move. What is it? } 14... Bh3
{ A brilliant move with the point being that   15.gxh3  will be met by  15...Qg6  and the d3-Knight hangs. }
15. Ne1
{ 15.gxh3  Qg6  16.Kh1  Qxd3  and Black is fine as the White King is not secure due to the pawns scattered. }
15... Qg6 16. Kh1 Raf8 { Adding more energy. } 17. f3
{ 17.gxh3  Rxf2  18.Rxf2  Rxf2  Threatening a devilish mate of... Rf1+ 19. Nf1 and Qg1 mate.  19.Qg4  Rxd2  20.Qxg6  hxg6  The Rook on the seventh rank is just killing White's pawns.  21.dxc6  Rxb2 =  And the endgame is completely equal as our Rook is active which compensates for the extra pawn of White. }
17... Bc8 18. dxc6 Rxc6 { And once again, the two Bishops rule the game. } *

